{
  "texts": [
    "While the DSA provides tools for setting the ground for protecting freedom of expression and pluralism of media by mandating that VLOPs identify systemic risks, it does not specifically target the protection of journalists and media professionals [22,54,136], despite acknowledging the importance media freedom as reported in Recital 47 and 81.",
    "Research approaches to evaluate DSA impact on disinformationHaving analyzed multi-dimensional critiques revealing meaningful gaps in the DSA's approach, undertaking comprehensive empirical research should assess its real-world efficacy across involved stakeholders.",
    "Specifically, the legal analysis flagged ambiguities in key definitions and inconsistencies in obligations across platforms.",
    "The technical review highlighted monitoring barriers, while the psychological critique called out assumptions on how false content spreads.",
    "The ethical lens questioned privatized speech regulation."
  ]
}